I used an inertia switch from a Ford Aerostar. They are located behind
the front passenger side kick panel (for those folks who frequent
self-serve wrecking yards). I wouldn't run an electric fuel pump without
some sort of safety switch.

-Rocky


tristan shaffer wrote:

E&B are right about the safety issue of an electric pump running on in
the event of an accident or stall. You could even add a
resettable crash sensor, like a modern car.
